Towards the end of his life he (Abû Muhammad Ruwaym) hid himself among the
rich and gained the Caliph’s confidence, but such was the perfection of his
spiritual rank that he was not thereby veiled from God. Hence Junayd
said：‘We are devotees occupied (with the world), and Ruwaym is a man occupied
(with the world) who is devoted (to God).’
